						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab preserved in the Museum.</hi></p>						

						<p>Sōmēśvara II—A.D. 1070.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is the same as No. 110 of <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XI, part I. It gives an interesting derivation of the name <hi rend="bold">Paṭṭadakal</hi> or <hi rend="bold">Paṭṭadakisuvoḷal.</hi> It says that the town was so called on account of its being the place of the coronations of the kings of the <hi rend="bold">Chālukya</hi> family. </p>						

						</summary>
